articles.author: David Shepardson, Joseph White
articles.description: Ford (F.N) autoworkers were set to begin heading back to work after the United Auto Workers (UAW) union reached a tentative labor deal with the company late Wednesday.
articles.title: Ford workers to return to work as UAW turns to GM, Stellantis

articles.author: Lucia Mutikani
articles.description: The U.S. economy grew almost 5% in the third quarter, again defying dire warnings of a recession, as higher wages from a tight labor market helped to fuel consumer spending and businesses restocked at a brisk clip to meet the strong demand.
articles.title: US economy delivers blockbuster performance in third quarter

articles.author: Diane Bartz
articles.description: Google executive Prabhakar Raghavan on Thursday detailed challenges the search and advertising giant faces from smaller rivals, describing efforts to avoid becoming "the next road kill."
articles.title: Google executive testifies innovation key to avoid becoming 'next road kill'

articles.author: Dawn Chmielewski
articles.description: Cultural phenomenon Taylor Swift helped fuel revenue at Universal Music Group (UMG.AS) in the third quarter, the world's largest record label said on Thursday.
articles.title: Taylor Swift helps fuel Universal Music Group's third-quarter revenue

articles.author: Deborah Sophia
articles.description: Investors will look for signs that U.S. fast-food chains, already contending with inflation-stung consumers preferring to dine at home, will also have to grapple with the explosive popularity of weight-loss drugs.
articles.title: Weight-loss drug worries add to US restaurants' weak traffic woes

articles.author: Nick Carey
articles.description: BP's (BP.L) electric vehicle charger unit is ordering $100 million worth of Tesla (TSLA.O) ultra-fast chargers for rollout in the United States, the first deployment of Tesla's chargers on an independent network, the companies said on Thursday.
articles.title: Tesla gets $100 mln US ultra-fast charger order from BP EV charging unit

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China has stepped up spending to replace Western-made technology with domestic alternatives as Washington tightens curbs on high-tech exports to its rival, according to government tenders, research documents and four people familiar with the matter.
articles.title: China rushes to swap Western tech with domestic options as U.S. cracks down

articles.author: Jonathan Saul, Stephen Farrell
articles.description: What lies in wait for Israeli ground troops in Gaza, security sources say, is a Hamas tunnel network hundreds of kilometres long and up to 80 metres deep, described by one freed hostage as "a spider's web" and by one expert as the "Viet Cong times 10".
articles.title: Hamas' tunnel city beneath Gaza - a hidden front line for Israel

articles.author: Richard Valdmanis, Gabriella Borter
articles.description: Maine authorities said on Thursday that 18 people were killed and 13 were injured when a man with a rifle attacked patrons at a bowling alley and a bar in the city of Lewiston the previous night.
articles.title: Maine mass shootings: Police scour Lewiston for suspect

articles.author: Joseph Ax
articles.description: A federal judge on Thursday ordered Georgia lawmakers to draw a new congressional map for the 2024 election, ruling that the current Republican-backed plan illegally diluted Black votes in violation of the Voting Rights Act.
articles.title: US judge orders new congressional map in Georgia, citing harm to Black voters
